	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=220402><span id= >Nimbu</span></a><br><span id=notbold>9 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I have one of these on my Shaman, for use with Rabid Bear.<br><br>Some facts:<br><br>* Shamans cannot deliver critical hits with melee weapons. There are no AAs for it, only for crits with certain spells.<br><br>* The usual hit with this weapon is 66, which conveniently is (2*DMG). Shamans don't get a damage bonus.<br><br>* Shamans are also on the &quot;caster&quot; melee table, shared with the other priests and indeed the INT casters. We do get skill caps of 200, higher than the other classes, but whether your ATK is 923 or 1523 you'll never see more than roughly 4.18 * DMG from a weapon, which in this case is 138.<br><br>* Shamans do get a self buff AA which allows Double Attack, plus gives 200 raw ATK. With this, I have occasionally doubled for 138 with this weapon, but it's eyewateringly rare to do so.<br><br>There is no way whatsoever to get 200+ hits from this weapon - the only tradeable weapon I've see go that high is the Dathor Great Hammer, which hits for 310 max.<br><br>Sadly, although this is a nice enough weapon, it's unlikely to be used too much in the 50s and 60s. Clerics generally use their summoned proccing hammers, druids rarely melee at all and shamans - well, it's fun enough to swing in between casts of Canni IV.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
